In [69]:
def EvalPoly(x, coefs):
    '''
     y = EvalPoly(x, coefs)
     
     Evaluates the linear model
     
       y = coefs[0] + coefs[1]*x + coefs[2]*x**2 + ... + coefs[n]*x**n
    '''
    y = np.zeros(np.shape(x))
    for idx,c in enumerate(coefs):
        y += c*x**idx
    return y

Functional MRI¶

Set up regressors¶

In [82]:
N = 1200 # number of samples
T = 120 # duration (seconds)
t = np.arange(N) * T/N
# Stimulus
a_stim = -np.cos(2*np.pi*3*t/T)
a_stim[a_stim>0] = 1.
a_stim[a_stim<=0] = 0.
plt.figure(figsize=[10,2])
plt.plot(a_stim); plt.xlabel('Time (s)'); plt.ylabel('Stimulus');
In [83]:
a_breathing = np.sin(2*np.pi*8*t/T)
a_breathing[a_breathing<0] = a_breathing[a_breathing<0]/3.
plt.figure(figsize=[10,2])
plt.plot(t, a_breathing); plt.xlabel('Time (s)'); plt.ylabel('Breathing');
In [84]:
a_heart = np.sin(2*np.pi*100*t/T)
a_heart[a_heart<0] = 0.
plt.figure(figsize=[10,2])
plt.plot(t, a_heart); plt.xlabel('Time (s)'); plt.ylabel('Heart Beat');
In [85]:

In [86]:

Gradient-Descent Solution¶

In [92]:
c = c0
y = y0
In [93]:
beta_gd = np.zeros(len(c))
In [94]:
# Gradient descent
iters = 500
kappa = 0.0001
for iter in range(iters):
    beta_gd -= kappa * A.T @(A@beta_gd-y)
In [95]:
print(beta_gd)
yy_gd = A @ beta_gd
